he large stainless steel feeding tray for the CFFS ironers is appreciated by all users. The CFFS ironers comply with the strictest industry safety regulations.Energy efficient: Ipso CFFS flatwork ironers offer you the most flexible programming options in order to ensure you the lowest energy consumptions whilst maintaining top ironing quality.Easy to service: The major components of the CFFS ironers are all easily accessible and maintenance and service is fast and economical.',NULL,'http://www.ipso.be/myImages/01/001/003/cffs500left.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(22,4,'Control options for flatwork ironers','Flexibility: The IPSO-controls allow the user to adapt several parameters to his needs, ensuring an ironing result that meets his standards.User friendly: The IPSO-controls are incredibly easy to understand, ensuring professional ironing quality with every ironing.',NULL,'http://www.ipso.be/myImages/01/001/006/controls-ironers.gif',1,NULL,NULL),(23,1,'HS Series Soft-mount High-speed','To provide their clients with washers with the best washability and offer proprietors the best quality wash, profitability, productivity and a simple and easy form of management. This has been the leitmotif which has led Girbau to develop the 6 series. The HS 6 series washer extractors are high speed and 100% Free Standing, do not require bolting down and reach spin speeds up to 1000 rpm.\n\nThey are available in the following capacities (ratio 1/9):  9kg (HS-6008), 14kg (HS-6013), 19kg (HS-6017), 25kg (HS-6023), 44kg (HS-6040), 63kg (HS-6057), 122kg (HS-6110)\n\nERGONOMIC AND SAFE DESIGN\n\nThe aesthetic design of the 6 Series washers is not satisfied with simply making your environment more pleasant. During the design, ergonomic and safety criteria have been considered. For example, the rounded corners avoid injuring operators, who may bump into the washer accidentally, and make the machine easier to clean.\n\nIn the HS-6057 and HS-6110 models, an optional tilting system (TILT system) enables you to load and unload it very easily. The TILT system is not only very efficient, but also requires very little maintenance and does not take up additional space.\n\nHS 6 Series incorporates:\n\n-MDS (Multidirectional springs): Allows spin cycle speeds greater than 350G in a silent and very stable way.\n\n-GDRIVE: Electronic system that allows optimal treatment for each type of fabric.\n\n-AQUAFALL:  Holes in the drum shovels allow additional water to enter like a waterfall – increasing cleaning action and reducing rinse cycle time.\n\n-AQUAMIXER:  Hot and cold water mixer that allows obtaining very precise bath temperatures.\n\n-JUST IN-LOAD: Allows to automatically calculate the quantity of water and the dosing time required to achieve the suitable chemical product concentration, according to the selected program and the weight of the load.\n\n-EASY LOAD: System to help loading and unloading operations of high-capacity washing machines. This option is applicable to HS-6057 and HS-6110 models.\n\n-Wet Cleaning Ready: HS-6013, HS-6017 and HS-6023 models with Inteli control display this distinctive logo.\nInteli control allows these washing machines to perform from intensive washing processes to extremely delicate processes to wash delicate linen such as wool.\n\nControls for coin-operated, OPL and professional processes\n\nThe HS 6 series is available with three control versions that allow you to respond to any washing need.\n\nCOIN: HS-6008 – HS-6013 – HS-6017 – HS-6023\n\nFor coin-op establishments. It has 4 individually modifiable programs. Pay system with coins or tokens. The clock option allows you to program prices according to the time of day and program.\n\nLOGI: HS-6008 – HS-6013 – HS-6017 – HS-6023\n\nFor OPL. It has 8 individually modifiable programs. The clock option allows you to program the desired start time. It has a crease-guard mode, selectable gradual cool-down and failure check and message alarm system.\n\nINTELI: HS-6013 – HS-6017 – HS-6023 – HS-6040 – HS-6057 – HS-6110\n\nIt allows infinite programming possibilities (20 standard programs and 79 free). It’s the ideal control for professional processes, including Wet Cleaning, Goretex, etc. The Inteli control allows you to save programs on a memory card and copy them onto other washing machines. The icons developed by Girbau make programming fast and easy.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/serie_6000_ok.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(24,1,'MG Series Hard-mount High-speed','The new 200G machines reduce residual moisture\n\nThe MG Series 6 washers are hard-mounted high speed machines (i.e. they require anchoring). With spin speeds of 750 rpm and a G factor of 200, they reduce residual moisture between 10 and 25% compared to other hard-mount washers with lower G factors.\n\nThey are available in the following capacities (ratio 1:10): 13kg (MG-613), 17kg (MG-617) and 23kg (MG-623).\n\n* LOGI PRO control: Designed for commercial laundries, it permits all washing parameters. LOGI PRO control incorporates the Just in Load function, which adjusts the water consumption and the dispensing time according to the program selected and the weight of the load.\n* COIN control: For coin-op laundries. It has 4 very easy to use programs that can be modified individually with different payment system options: Vending (via a central payment unit), Coin counter or Button.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/MGlogiPro-web.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(25,1,'MS Series Hard-mount Medium-speed','6 MS Series, experience and innovation\n\nTo provide their clients with washers with the best washability and offer proprietors the best quality wash, profitability, productivity and a simple and easy form of management. This has been the leitmotif which has led Girbau to develop the 6 series.\n\nThe 6 MS series, requires bolting down, reach speeds up to 600 rpm and are available in the following capacities: 10kg (MS-610), 13kg (MS-613), 17kg (MS-617) and 23kg (MS-623).\n\nThe best washability in the market\n\nGirbau started from the basis that if each of the factors influencing the wash process was improved (mechanical action, chemical action, time and temperature) together with an efficiently managed water supply they would have the washers with the best washability on the market. Added to this challenge was that of designing the most productive, profitable, robust, easy to use, ergonomic and eco-friendly machines.\n\nThe most important features on the 6 series directly related to washability (Sinner diagram) are:\n\nMechanical action\n- The ratio between the depth and the diameter in the series 6 washing machine drum guarantees optimum mechanical action.\n- Girbau has made a study of peripheral speeds seeking the optimum speed with regard to the movement of the blades which agitate the washing. Thus achieving the best mechanical action possible to assure the maximum amount of dirt is removed.\n\n- Aquafall system (perforated blades): a number of large exterior holes on the rear side of the blades next to the rotating drum produce a pumping action and generate a deluge of water as each blade passes. The waterwheel effect permits the intake of additional water and improves rinsing.\n\nTemperature:\n- The new washers incorporate the Aquamixer system, a hot and cold water mixer. This enables the required water temperature to be reached both quickly and accurately (+/- 2°C).\n\nTime\n- The new controls Coin (for coin-op), Logi (for OPL) enable the wash programmes to be adapted in terms of users needs, achieving faster and more appropriate processes for the type of fabric being treated.\n\n- The spin cycle finished, all the 6 series washers, apart from the 13kg model, have an immediate brake and door opening, eliminating pointless waiting time and improving productivity.\n\nChemical action:\n-Chemical products don’t come into direct contact with the laundry but are previously diluted in a dispenser. The previous dilution process ensures that the laundry receives careful treatment.\n\n- The arrangement of the compartments in the dispenser logically follows the wash process, avoiding confusion.\n\n- The MS 6 series washers incorporate 4 external dosings.\n\n- Ozone: all the 6 series machines are suitably equipped to work with ozone processes, requesting the Viton seal option.\n\nWater:\nThe four previous factors require an efficiently managed water supply as a dilution agent. Girbau has optimised the use of water by means of:\n- The least possible distance between the inner and outer drums: provides considerable soaking capacity with relatively small water levels.\n- The absence of heaters chambers: avoids unnecessary volumes of water at each filling.\n- Drain next to the outer drum on the static part: minimises the volume of water between the outer drum and the drain and avoids any damage to the valve caused by vibrations.\n\nNeeding less water directly corresponds to reduced detergent consumption for the same concentrations, reduced thermal energy consumption for the same temperatures and reduced filling time.\nIn addition, Girbau’s GDrive (complete acceleration, speed and out-of-balance control) represents a great saving on motor energy.\n\nErgonomics and Ecology\n\nThis optimisation of resources used in the wash process makes the 6 series washers the most environmentally friendly. All the materials used in the fabrication of the washers are recyclable.\nThe 6 series washers have also been designed with the same robustness as Girbau’s 4000 series, well-known for its excellent durability and resistance.\nThe 6 series prototypes have passed all the life tests they have been submitted to (for example, they have exceeded more than 40 million wash cycles).\nThe ergonomics have also been taken into account.\nThe reduced depth of the drum makes unloading easier.\n\nControls for coin-operated, OPL and professional processes\n\nThe MS 6 series is available with two control versions that allow you to respond to any washing need.\nCOIN: For coin-op establishments. It has 4 individually modifiable programs. Pay system with coins or tokens. The clock option allows you to program prices according to the time of day and program.\nLOGI: For OPL. It has 8 individually modifiable programs. The clock option allows you to program the desired start time. It has a crease-guard mode, selectable gradual cool-down and failure check and message alarm system.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/SERIE-MS_web.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(26,1,'LS Series Hard-mount Medium-speed','The hard-mount LS range is a new dimension in washer-extractor design, the most reliable and efficient on the market. They are both environmentally friendly and quiet. Three control options for complete customer satisfaction.\n\nReliable machines built to last\nThe frame is structurally reinforced, primed and sprayed in highly resistant epoxy paint\n\nSuperior protection against harsh chemicals\nGirbau’s inner and outer drums are AISI-304 stainless steel to help extend the life of each machine.\n\n* The Wash Quality you need\n* User friendly from day one\nVersatility, accuracy and control to meet your requirements\n\nCOMMERCIAL\n\n*\n\nSM STANDARD Microprocessor control\n\nINDUSTRIAL\n\n*\n\nPM PROGRAMMABLE Microprocessor control\n\nSELF-SERVICE\n\n* CM COIN Microprocessor control\n\nHeatings Alternatives:\n\n* Hot water\n* Electric heating\n* Steam heating',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/LS-32-55.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(27,1,'PCH Series','PCH Model: PCH-15 / PCH-25 / PCH-35 / PCH-45 / PCH-63 / PCH-84\n\nHigh speed barrier washer extractor with two opposed doors.\nCapacity: 15/25/35/45/63/84 kg.\n\nG Factor 350.\n\nInner and outer drums, doors and external panels in stainless steel.\nInstallation: No holding-down required.\nSafety doors: with electrical lock.\n\n* Microprocessor control.\n* Heating: Electric, Steam.\nLW Model: LW-100 / LW-150 / LW-200\n\nBarrier washer extractor with suspended system absorbing up to 95% vibration\nCapacity: 105 / 150 / 205 kg, ratio 1:10\nG Factor superior 300\nInner and outer drum and rest of elements in contact with the bath in AISI-304 quality 18/8 stainless steel.\n3 compartment inner durm.\nDouble safety door-lock.\nAutomatic door position.\n\n* Microprocessor control.\n* Steam heating.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/pch.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(28,1,'RT Series','Water recovery tank\n\nRe-using the water from the rinse phase for the following pre-wash and wash phases allows the water consumption to be reduced by 40%.\n\nThis is by no means a marketing ploy, but a genuine concern which Girbau has always expressed for the environment.\nThe ISO-14001 and EMAS certificates held by Girbau are an affirmation of this fact.\n\nGirbau’s RT water recovery tank is easy to install. The tank is delivered with a kit including pump, hoses for connection and a guide for easy installation.\n\nBy optimizing the energy consumption of their installations and enjoying the subsequent cost-effective benefits, amounts to a respect for the environment.\n\n* RT-500, applicable to washer-extractor models LS-355 PM, HS-6040 PM, HS-6055 PM.\n* RT-1000, applicable to washer-extractor models HS-6110 PM',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/HS6110_&_Recuperador_Baixa.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(29,1,'PS/PSP Series','Efficient, Easy to use, Safe Operation, High Throughput, Modern design and Ecological\n\nA flatwork ironer with unique features. Efficient, Easy to use, Safe operation, High throughput, Modern design and Ecological, all combine to offer a top level of performance.\n\nUnique and exclusive Innovations\n* Autospeed (Mod. PS-32 & PS/PSP-51) automatically adjusting the ironing speed depending on type of material and humidity.\n* Kinematic strap tensioning system, assuring an exceptional ironing quality and smoothness.\n* Cylinder is fabricated in steel, machined, polished and finished in chrome.\n* Powerful extractor fan.\nTechnical Features\n* Return feed design requires minimum installation space.\n* Nomex ironing straps.\n* High throughput as linen is in contact with cylinder through a high proportion of the roller circumference.\n* Minimum acoustic level.\n* Thermal insulation of casting ceramic fibre.\n* Ergonomically designed control panel.\n* Safety hand guard.\n* Emergency stop.\n* Conforms the European safety standards (CE 89/392).\n\nPSP version with Built-in Length Folder\nTwo folding options:\n\n* Folding by pre-setting the size of the item.\n* Automatic folding, a photo-cell sizes the previous item.\n\n* The length folded items are fed out on discharge bands at the front of the ironer.\n\nControl panels:\n* GIRBAU Electronic Microprocessor PS-32, PS/PSP-51\n\nHeating alternatives:\n* Electric: PS-32, PS/PSP-51.\n* Propane, natural gas: PS-32, PS/PSP-51,\n* Steam: PS/PSP-5119, PS/PSP-5132.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/PS-PSP_web.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(30,1,'P Series','QUALITY FINISHING IN THE SMALLEST SPACE\n\nEFFICIENCY IN SIMPLICITY\n\nThe P-2510 and P-2514 ironers from Girbau are perfect for ironing flat linen.\nIts front linen entry and outlet allows for installation along the wall help to make the most out of the space destined for the laundry area.\nThe operation is extremely simple. A single operator can activate the machine with a pedal.\nThe cylinder padding and Nomex cover, guarantee a uniform pressure, thus assuring the best ironing.\n\nThe user electronically selects the desired temperature and adjusts the speed of the cylinder from a control panel.\n\nSAFETY AND DURABILITY\n\nThe Girbau P-2510 and P-2514 ironers have various built-in safety measures: hand guards, a safety mechanism that activates in the event of a power cut, and a safety thermostat to prevent overheating.\n\nA system of separators placed at the linen outlet prevents the laundry from wrapping around the cylinder.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/p25_WEB.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(31,1,'Compact Series','Girbau’s Compact 5-in-1: a compact flatwork ironer for smaller spaces\n\nGirbau’s Compact is a new high production compact flatwork ironer that makes it possible to feed*, iron, dry, fold and stack* in a small space (*option).\n\nWith the Compact every kind of flat linen can be ironed and folded while saving energy using a carefully designed temperature control system.\n\nTo ensure that the linen is fed in effectively, the new flatwork ironer has an on-table suction system that helps to stretch the linen taut so that it enters the ironer ready-smoothed.\n\nIt allows the user to work with one, two or four work lanes. In this way, one lane can be used for sheets, two for table linen and four for small items.\n\nVX3P STANDARD OPTION\n1 or 2 folds on 1, 2, 3 or 4 lanes + 1, 2 or 3 cross-folds on 1 lane\n\nMX3P MULTILINE OPTION\n1 or 2 folds on 1, 2, 3 or 4 lanes + 1, 2 or 3 cross-folds on 1 lane, or 1 or 2 cross-folds on 2 lanes.\n\nThe folds are performed using jets of air and reversible conveyors.\n\nThe new flatwork ironer lets the user choose from 20 programs and create 20 more user-defined programs.\n\nThe Compact is extremely easy to use.  All the ironing parameters, alterations or incidents that arise during the process can be controlled using an intuitive touch screen.\n\nThe new Girbau 5-in-1 ironing system is available in gas, electricity or steam versions.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/Compact_WEB.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(32,1,'STI Series','Optimal drying performance with minimun consumption\n\nEfficient, environmentally friendly drying tumblers with a large load capacity and built to last.\n\nAvailables with the following capacities: 13,6kg (STI-14), 22,68kg (STI-23), 34,02kg (STI-34), 54,43kg (STI-54) & 77,11kg (STI-77).\n\nMachines built to last\n\nThe stainless steel drum, supported by industrial bearings, is capable of handling the most demanding work loads and help to extend the life of the machine.\n\nSafe and easy to use\n\nModels STI-23/34/54/77 come equipped as standard with a rotating reverse system which together with the large doors guarantees the easiest and best possible linen unloading.\nThe door is closed by magnets.\nThe large and easy-access lint filters, as well as the information regarding the need to clean them which appears on the display, guarantee a high performance from the machine.\nThe machine’s automatic crease-guard function is activated at the end of the cycle.\n\nThe microprocessor control achieves an optimum drying efficiency and excellent laundry care\n\nAll the machines, whatever model, are controlled by a microprocessor.\n\nStandard control(S)\nAllows the cycles to be programmed in two different ways:\n- temperature / time\n- temperature / drying degree (automatic drying)\n\nIndicated in both case is the cooling time, etc.\n\nCoin-op control (AUT-ME)\nAllows for a choice of three different types of drying: high / medium / low\n\nVending control (AUT-VE)\nAllows for a choice of three different types of drying: high / medium / low\n\nHeating Alternatives\n\nSTI-14  Natural Gas, Propane Gas and Electricity\nSTI-23  Natural Gas, Propane Gas, Electricity and Steam\nSTI-34  Natural Gas, Propane Gas, Electricity and Steam\nSTI-54  Natural Gas, Propane Gas, Electricity, Steam and Hot oil\nSTI-77  Natural Gas, Propane Gas, Steam and Hot oil',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/gamma_assec.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(33,1,'SLI Series','GIRBAU SLI-9 Drying Tumbler - A NEW DIMENSION IN DRYING TECHNOLOGY\n\nOPTIMUM DRYING WITH A REDUCED ENERGY CONSUMPTION\nThe SLI-9 drying tumbler combines maximum drying performance with optimum energy efficiency. Its reliability and durability makes this machine indispensable as regards the profitability of any laundry.\n\nAvailable with the following capacity: 9kg (SLI-9).\n\nA robust design\n\nThe door opens and closes easily thanks to an ergonomically designed handle and a magnetic closing system.\n\nLoading and unloading is made easier by the extra large door.\n\nOptimum management\nThe microprocessor built into the dryer carries out complete diagnostics of all the machine’s parameters to achieve maximum profitability and optimise the drying process.\n\nEasy maintenance access\n\nEasy access to all the components in SLI drying tumbler makes it all the more easy to carry out maintenance tasks.\nPractically all the components are right at hand by simply opening one panel.\nThe lint filter is also easily accessed. A message appears on the control panel display to indicate when the filter is dirty thus guaranteeing the cleaning process is carried out, essential for the dryer’s optimum performance.\n\nRobustness, durability and energy saving mean maximum profitability\n\nThe materials used in this machine’s construction together with its robust design guarantee its resilience against the harshest of conditions for many years.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/SLI9-WEB.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(34,1,'SE-7','Compact, efficient, space saver dryer, low on energy cost.\n* Capacity 7.5 kg (15 lbs.) dry linen.\n* Cylinder and outer cabinet in durable enamel finish.\n* Large diameter front loading door with safety device.\n* Built-in lint filter, easy to clean.\n\nStandard Features:\n\n* Safety micro-switch on door.\n* Automatic stop minute-timer.\n* Temperature selector.\n* Thermal overload motor protection.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/se7.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(35,4,'Form finisher','Easy ironing for garments\n\nS/AV model\nSelf-contained form finisher with standard frame.\nBuilt-in 15 ltr electric boiler, feed pump and fan.\n\nS/VC model\nAutomatic form finsher with built-in fan for connection to central steam supply.\n\nBoth models include 2 manual clamps for jackets and 2 sleeve stretchers.\n\nCombi machine for finishing jackets and trousers\n\nA fully automatic unit which enables with just one operator to rapidly finish jackets, coats, raincoats, etc.. and trousers simultaneously, with remarkable results.\nThe machine is equipped with one work station with the automatic positioning of a \"form finisher\" and a \"topper\" alternatively.\n\nS/MTA model\nSelf-contained form finisher with built-in 12 kW boiler.\n\nS/MTV model\nTo be connected to central steam (20/25 kg/h, at 4-6 bar)',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/Svc.gif',1,NULL,NULL),(36,4,'Ironing table','Ideal systems for laundries, clothing manufacturers, etc....\n\nVery easy to use and to install.\n\nS/AAR Model\n\nSelf-contained automatic unit with vacuum ironing board heated by electric elements.\nBuilt-in boiler to supply steam for the iron.\n\nS/AVR Model\n\nSelf-contained automatic unit with steaming and vacuum ironing board.\nElectric boiler to produce steam for the board and the iron.\n\nS/AVC Model\n\nAutomatic unit with steaming and vacuum ironing board to be connected to central steam supply.\n\nIron included.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/Saar.gif',1,NULL,NULL),(37,4,'Utility press','Suitable for Dry cleaners, Industrial laundries.\n\nThe presses are manufactured in manual (S/MP4) and air-operated (S/EP4) versions.\n\nManual top buck motion on model S/MP4.\nTop buck motion by compressed air on model S/EP4.\n\nBalanced top buck, mounted on a bar with ball bearings.\n\nBoth bucks with steam, bottom buck with vacuum.\n\nAdjustable buck pressure control.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/Smp4.gif',1,NULL,NULL),(38,4,'Shirt equipment','Cold Spotting board\n\nModels S/F and S/FC\nIn stainless steel.\nBuilt-in vacuum.\n2 spotting guns with independent circuits.\n1 air drying gun.\n1 vacuum swing arm with stainless steel spotting form.\n\nShirt Press\n\nModel S/ICP, specially designed for collar and cuff finishing.\nModel S/IDS, specially designed for front and back finishing.\nPolished top buck, heated lower buck.\nTo be connected to central steam and compressed air.\nBuilt-in vacuum.\n\nIndustrial form finisher model S/IMC\nAutomatic and pneumatic form finisher\nSuitable for finishing casual shirts and jackets in general.\nMobile front fixing clamp heated with blow.\nMachine to be connected to central steam and compressed air.\n\nShirt Folding table\n\nModel S/TPC\nWith heated adjustable collar block and arms for folding sleeves.\nIdeal for combination with form finisher.\n\nMinisilc electric steam generator',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/s-imc.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(39,4,'Spotting boards','Cold Spotting board\n\nModels S/F and S/FC\nIn stainless steel.\nBuilt-in vacuum.\n2 spotting guns with independent circuits.\n1 air drying gun.\n1 vacuum swing arm with stainless steel spotting form.\n\nShirt Press\n\nModel S/ICP, specially designed for collar and cuff finishing.\nModel S/IDS, specially designed for front and back finishing.\nPolished top buck, heated lower buck.\nTo be connected to central steam and compressed air.\nBuilt-in vacuum.\n\nIndustrial form finisher model S/IMC\nAutomatic and pneumatic form finisher\nSuitable for finishing casual shirts and jackets in general.\nMobile front fixing clamp heated with blow.\nMachine to be connected to central steam and compressed air.\n\nShirt Folding table\n\nModel S/TPC\nWith heated adjustable collar block and arms for folding sleeves.\nIdeal for combination with form finisher.\n\nMinisilc electric steam generator',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/s-fc.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(40,4,'Accessory items','Cold Spotting board\n\nModels S/F and S/FC\nIn stainless steel.\nBuilt-in vacuum.\n2 spotting guns with independent circuits.\n1 air drying gun.\n1 vacuum swing arm with stainless steel spotting form.\n\nShirt Press\n\nModel S/ICP, specially designed for collar and cuff finishing.\nModel S/IDS, specially designed for front and back finishing.\nPolished top buck, heated lower buck.\nTo be connected to central steam and compressed air.\nBuilt-in vacuum.\n\nIndustrial form finisher model S/IMC\nAutomatic and pneumatic form finisher\nSuitable for finishing casual shirts and jackets in general.\nMobile front fixing clamp heated with blow.\nMachine to be connected to central steam and compressed air.\n\nShirt Folding table\n\nModel S/TPC\nWith heated adjustable collar block and arms for folding sleeves.\nIdeal for combination with form finisher.\n\nMinisilc electric steam generator',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/minisilc.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(41,4,'Trolleys','GIRBAU Wet linen trolley\n\nCapacity up to 250 litres.\nBuilt in high-density polyethylene.\nSupported by a metallic base in tubular frame and EPOXY painted.\nWith four swivel casters.\n\nGIRBAU Kangaroo trolley\n\nTo carry soiled and/or clean linen.\nTilting shelves.\nRound tubular zinc frame.\n\nGIRBAU Shelf trolley\n\nFor intermediate operations, and as an addition to, or instead of, fixed shelves.\nTubular frame EPOXY painted.\nEasy to dismantle.\n\nGIRBAU Moving bottom trolley\n\nRound tubular zinc frame.\nProvided with resinous PVC mesh fixed to the frame by four high resistance springs.\nFour nylon casters, two fixed and two swivel.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/thp96.gif',1,NULL,NULL),(42,4,'Loading system','Inclined loading Conveyor ICP-4\n\nInclined conveyor with 4 compartments of 50 kg (110 lb).\nIt is the appropriate element to load a batch washer in a simple and precise manner.\nIncluding automatic weighing.\nUpper sides and separator scoops in stainless steel, lower sides in enamelled plate.\nAdvance restrictor microswitch and photoelectric cell.\n\nThe handling system comprises:\n\n* A loading area with various loading stations and electronic weighing\n* Dirty linen arrival conveyors\n* Empty bags lift\n* Automatic fastening system of the bags with a storage using a minimum of space\n* Full bags lift\n* Outlet to batch washer or washing machines\n* Return circuit and empty bags storage.\nControl:\n\nWith a management PC that controls all the working parameters and deals with the operation of the handling loading system.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/ICP4.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(43,4,'Batch washer','New mechanical features, highly efficient, maximum flexibility, optimum control\n\nIn response to the needs of the marketplace, the laundry sector has had to adapt itself to the demands of its customers: new fabrics, new processes, new production needs, sanitary demands in hospitals, etc.\nGIRBAU has developed a machine capable of responding to all of today’s demands and adapt to the future demands of the market.\nThe modular system of the TBS-50 batch washer allows it to adapt to all types of installations (hotels, hospital, industrial laundries, etc.). Its versatility and flexibility converts the TBS-50 batch washer into an investment for the present and the future.\nGIRBAU invites you to discover the difference.\n\nNew mechanical Features\n* Accurate design of all components.\n* Simple and rugged design for a rigid, stable and long lasting machine.\n* Support bearings at inlet and outlet openings, located away from the wash bath.\n* Forward positioned motor drive, sprocket and crown, having no contact with the wash bath.\n* Inverter controlled motor.\n* Minimal installation requirements, saving time and money.\n\nHighly Efficient\n\n* Centre transfer of goods.\n* Maximum diameter on transfer opening.\n* Important mechanical action through the 7 wash beaters on each drum.\n* Total bath separation by double seal between each module.\n* Direct heating on each washing module with built-in silencer.\n* 4 Separate dosing inlets for each module.\n* Minimum effect in the natural environment.\nMaximum Flexibility\n* Each module incorporates both an inner and outer drum, loading capacity 50Kg linen (ratio 1:45).\n* Totally external flow or counter-flow baths.\n* Each module can be provided with: 1 weir box, 1 level sensor, 1 temperature probe, 1 heating system, 4 product inlets, 2 water inlets, 2 drains, 2 ducts and 2 recirculation pumps.\n* Adjustment and control of the individual wash baths and its levels.\n* Each module is fitted with a temperature probe.\nOptimum control\n* 99 Washing programmes and 999 customer codes.\n* PC in central board away from the batch washer, incorporating an efficient output control.\n* Display and control in real time of all batches in process, each bath temperature and the different dosings.\n* Alarms and messages on display, with complete protection against wrong operation and entry of incorrect parameters.\n* Up to 9 auxiliary internal programmes for working situations without PC.\n\nThe design of the TBS-50 batch washer ensures conformity with the most demanding world standards in terms of safety and it is provided with the CE (Europe) certification.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/ECOTUNNEL-low.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(44,4,'Water extraction press','Suitable for pressing linen batches from a batch washer\n\nLoading capacity 50 kg (110 lb).\nVersatile, simple and reliable operation.\nOptimal extraction press for high productivity and efficiency.\nAll parts in contact with the linen are in superior grade AISI-304 stainless steel.\n\nMultiple pressures\n\nHighly efficient oil dynamic circuit permits pressing between 6 to 35 bar.\n\nThe press forms a round cake with a flat base. With high capacity drainage facilities, a quick, gentle and excellent extraction of water is achieved for all types of linen.\n\nThe SPR-50 single stage press is available in three different positioning options at the batch washer outlet:\n\n* in-line version.\n* turns to right version.\n* turns to left version.\nEasy Installation and low maintenance\n\nThe SPR-50 water extraction press is delivered completely assembled and factory tested which facilitates problem free installation.\n\nMost of the SPR-50 press electrical components are the same as those used in TBS-50 batch washer and ST-100 batch dryer and are inter-changeable facilitating easy and convenient service.\n\nThe highest safety level\n\nThe design of the press ensures conformity with the most demanding world standards in terms of safety.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/SPR50.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(45,4,'Batch dryer','Excellent drying process: Maximum output and efficiency, low energy consumption.\n\nThe ST-100 batch dryer has been designed for the complete separating, conditioning, and drying of laundry and textile products.\n\nLoading capacity 100 kg (220 lbs.) dry linen (ratio 1:25).\n\nSturdy and simple\n\nThe simplicity of its design and the sturdiness of its construction makes for maximum durability with low maintenance.\n\nThe chassis is constructed with steel sides finished with high resistant epoxy paint. All the materials which come in contact with the laundry are made of AISI 304 stainless steel.\n\nThe large robust drum is supported by a set of guide wheels which give it a precise and silent operation, allowing for rotation reversals in both directions.\n\nThe SPIROTILT-GIRBAU system is the only one to unload without tilting and with the fan stopped.\n\nThe ST-100 dryer has the SPIROTILT-GIRBAU a revolutionary system which optimizes the drying process and facilitates the unloading of the laundry.\nWith the slight drum inclination of only 2.5º and the incorporation of inclined blades, the best drying process is obtained along with the best unloading system.\n\nThe SPIROTILT-GIRBAU system converts the ST-100 dryer into the one which most respects the environment. It avoids the unnecessary operation of the fan, with an important energy savings and without bringing lint into the air.\nWorking conditions are considerably improved in an environment without lint which brings great benefits to the health of employees.\n\nHeating systems:\n\n* Steam\n* Hot Oil\n* Gas\n\nFlexible programming\nThe ST-100 dryer has 16 different drying programs. Each program includes 8 phases.\n\nThe design of the ST-100 dryer ensures conformity with the most demanding world standards in terms of safety and it is provided with the CE (Europe) certification.\n\nA wide range of options:\n\n* Automatic cleaning of the lint filter\n* Thermostatic Sprinkler\n* Teflon covering of the drum interior\n* Cool-down cycle and temperature control\n* Pedestals according to the necessary height\nPass-through ST-100A Dryer\n\nGIRBAU ST-100A pass-through dryer incorporates an inclined loading conveyor, which permits the machine to function in a totally independent manner.\nThe ST-100A is prepared in a way to be easily adapted in the future to an installation with the TBS BATCH WASHER SYSTEM.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/ST100.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(46,4,'Distribution Conveyor','CEDD Model\n\nThe CEDD shuttle-lifting conveyor is the appropriate machine to distribute laundry batches coming from a press installed at the outlet of a batch washer.\nIt is provided with two loading tables of 1100 mm (43.3 inch) width, and 1280 mm (50.4 inch) length\n\nCEDD conveyor Control Panel, Model CEDD-CTR\n\nControl panel appropriate for controlling the Girbau shuttle lifting Conveyor, as well as the connection and communication of data from the press and dryers.\nThis connection box contains the necessary devices to regulate the operating voltage, as well as all the necessary parts for the electrical interconnections between the motors and sensors of the distribution conveyors and the panel.\nInside is housed the control PLC.\n\nFD - FDD Protection Fence\n\nProtection fence adapted to the operation area of the distribution conveyor between the press and the dryers, creating a safe environment.\nIncludes access door with opening sensor.\nWhen the access door is opened, the moving parts of conveyor and the surrounding area stop.\n\nIt complies with the UNE-EN ISO 10472 standard for industrial laundry machinery safety.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/CEDD.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(47,4,'Conveyor system','Conveyor for linen transport\n\nA conveyor belt with a width of 800 mm.\nIts chassis is built of welded, bolted steel profiles, finished with rustproof paint.\nPVC band with a flexible internal section, a rough band with great mechanical resistance and high damp-resistance.\nSides in AISI-304 stainless steel.\n\nWe differentiate two models:\n\nHT Horizontal Conveyor IT Inclined Conveyor',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/h%20t.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(48,1,'LW Series','LW Model: LW-100 / LW-150 / LW-200\n\nBarrier washer extractor with suspended system absorbing up to 95% vibration\nCapacity: 105 / 150 / 205 kg, ratio 1:10\nG Factor superior 300\nInner and outer drum and rest of elements in contact with the bath in AISI-304 quality 18/8 stainless steel.\n3 compartment inner durm.\nDouble safety door-lock.\nAutomatic door position.\n\n* Microprocessor control.\n* Steam heating.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/Luniwash.bmp',1,NULL,NULL),(49,4,'Flatwork ironer PSN-80','HIGH EFFICIENCY AND QUALITY WITH PSN-80 FLATWORK IRONERS\n\nThe new PSN-80 GIRBAU flatwork ironers generation represents a new standard in reliability, quality and energy efficiency.\n\nUnique and exclusive Innovations\n\nGirbau’s experience of about 40 years in the ironers’ manufacture, the use of state-of-the-art technologies and the continuous improvement that has always distinguished Girbau’s trade mark, are evident in the PSN-80. The maximum output and quality, a reliability beyond doubt and an assured profit will improve the efficiency and competitiveness of your processes.\n\nPSN-80 Girbau is available in 3 types of heating: STEAM, THERMAL OIL and GAS.\n\nGIRBAU GUARANTEE: THE SATISFACTION OF OUR CUSTOMERS\nThe good result of its predecessors, PS-700, PS-800 and PS-80, in production in hundreds of laundries all round the world, many of them still working after 25 years, is a source of satisfaction for our customers and, of course, our best guarantee.\n\nPSN-80 GAS: SAVINGS OPERATION\n\nPSN-80 GAS: A good example of technology applied to obtain the maximum efficiency and profitability with the maximum environmental respect.\nOur PSN-80 is equipped with the market’s most efficient boiler built in an ironer. With an output higher than 90%, you will obtain a substantial reduction in the energy consumption and you will eliminate the inconveniences involved in having a boiler room such as cost, maintenance, space used, installation costs, etc.\nNo doubt, PSN-80 GIRBAU GAS will be your best investment.\n\nWORKING WITH THE PSN-80 IS EASY\n\nWorking with a Girbau PSN-80 flatwork ironer is easy and comfortable. The electronic programmable microprocessor control provides maximum consistent control and perfect adaptation to the user’s specific needs. It incorporates: Autospeed® system, manual mode operation, operation mode with programmed speeds, operation mode for ribbon replacement, temperature display of each chest ironing surface, display of cylinder real speed, etc.\n\nWhen designing the PSN-80, Girbau took into account the specifications of the feeders and folders from the leading manufacturers.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/psn80frontal.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(50,4,'Flatwork ironer PC-120','Technology at the service of performance\n\nThe Girbau PC-120 flatwork ironer, 1200 mm. roller diameter,  is proof that not everything has already been invented in ironing.\n\nWith our commitment to constant improvement, and with performance, quality and efficiency as our goal, Girbau presents a flatwork ironer that is indispensable for businesses with high production loads and where profitability is not at odds with quality.\n\nThe rigid tray has been a high quality feature of Girbau ironing for 35 years, and the PC-120 demonstrates that experience, together with technological progress, is the best foundation on which to build.\n\nThe durability and performance of this flatwork ironer combine with the extensive benefits of programming with Inteli control, allowing the user to control the speed, the temperature, the motor consumption, the speed differences between rollers, the oil temperature or the steam exhaust.\n\nThe benefits of experience, together with cutting-edge technology, are within your reach with the PC-120.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/PC120.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(51,4,'Feeding machines','GIRBAU Automatic sheet feeder DRF\n\nThis is a new generation feeder for ironing processes with high production that guarantees great quality for items of any size. It has 3 automatic feeding stations with height-adjustable clamps.\n\nThe new DRF is a highly versatile feeder that adapts to the production needs of the moment. So, it can work on 1 lane, 2 lanes or on 1 or 2 lanes without distinction at 2, 3 or 4 working stations. The DRF automatically identifies the width of a fed item and centers it on the lanes used.\nFor feeding small pieces, the feeding stations with clamps are moved, leaving a suction table for manual feeding visible.\n\nApart from large production, the DRF guarantees high feeding quality. The clamps deposits the item on the ruler and with a rotating movement, lays it down on the suction feeding conveyor.\n\nAnother advantage of the DRF is that it doesn’t need the construction of a pit hole. The pieces move towards the upper part of the machine avoiding contact with the ground.\nThus, the DRF can be installed in any kind of installation in a simple and easy way.\n\nGIRBAU Small pieces feeder DRM\n\nCan be installed before any ironer; can either feed small pieces and large pieces.\nThe articles are fed manually on a feeding conveyor which insures the connection with the ironer feeding board, the spreading is insured by horizontal vacuum suction, one roller bar with two rolls with auto-centring device for each lane.\nSpeed synchronisation by impulse generator.\nAir collector and lint filter.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/drf.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(52,1,'Folders/FL Series','GIRBAU Air jet compact folder FL Series range\n\nSuitable machine to carry out 1,2 or 3 primary folds in 1 or 4 lanes and 1,2 or 3 crossfolds in 1 lane (3rd crossfold on stacker).\n\nWorking width 3000, 3300 or 3500 mm depending on the ironer.\nFull safety guards, interlocks and emergency stop buttons.\nAll measurements made by self-cleaning photocells.\nAC frequency inverter drive with soft start and variable speed features.\nComplete control of the folder through PLC.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/FL.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(53,4,'Stackers','GIRBAU Automatic Flap Sheet Stacker Mod. VOL\n\nCan be adapted behind a compact folder.\nIt stacks the items depending on the initially selected quantity and it discharges them onto a storage conveyor.\nWhen the predetermined number of pieces is reached, the conveyor moves forward.\nOptimal protection for operators by side covers, transparent guards and emergency stop.\n\nGIRBAU Automatic Sheet Stacker Mod. ROT\n\nCan be adapted behind a compact folder.\nIt makes a third crossfold, stacks pieces in a predetermined number and delivers the stacks on a conveyor.\nA photocell measures the pieces.\nA mechanical blade half-folds and introduces the pieces in the clamp.\nThis clamp turns on 270º and stacks the article on a deliver conveyor. When the predetermined number of pieces is reached, the conveyor moves forward.\nOptimal protection for operators by side covers, transparent guards and emergency stop.\n\nAP-LITE\n\nA stacker designed as an accessory to the FL-Lite folders. Low maintenance and easily adjustable flap stacking that is simple and effective.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/APILADORS.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(54,1,'FT Series','Polyvalent Towel & Form pieces Folder FT-VEST range\n\nTwo feeding tables with slight suction.\nFolding table 1200 x 1500 mm.\nFolding sizes: length 220 to 520 mm, width 180 to 410 mm.\nFolding by flaps.\nSorting of items by 3 store conveyors of 1300 mm (3 to 6 piles) with levelling and pressing systems.\nStacker adjustable by quantity.\nTorn and stain sorting device.\nFully safety guards.\nExtra folding bridge (length above 1500 mm up to 1800 mm).\n\nPolyvalent Towel & Form pieces Folder FT-POLY range\n\nFeeding table with slight suction.\nFolding table 1200 x 1500 mm.\nFolding sizes: length 220 to 520 mm, width 180 to 410 mm.\nFolding by flaps.\nSorting of items by 2,3 or 4 store conveyors of 1300 mm (3 to 6 piles) with levelling and pressing systems.\nStacker adjustable by quantity.\nTorn and stain sorting device.\nFully safety guards.\nExtra folding bridge (length above 1500 mm up to 1800 mm).\n\nFT-MAXI Independent folder for articles of towelling or similar items\n\nProduction up to 1,200 articles per hour, depending on the item inserted, the method of folding and the skill of the operator.\n\nFeatures:\n- Manual feeding on feeder table with two lengthwise folds and one or two cross-folds, and stacked on three independent conveyors.\n- Primary folding using an air jet, and cross-folding using a reversing system.\n- New easy maintenance folding table.\n- Capacity for articles of linen up to 2350 x 1200 mm.\n\nFT-LITE Folder for towelling items, airline blankets and similar articles\n\nProduction of up to 1,000 articles/hour, depending on the type of item inserted, the folding method and the skill of the operator.\n\nFeatures.\n- Capacity for articles of linen up to 1200 x 2400 mm.\n- Manual feeding on the feeder table.\n- 1, 2 or 3 lengthwise folds and 1 cross-fold.\n- Lengthwise fold in half or French-type fold.\n- Single stacking on conveyor.\n- Includes a top conveyor for ejection and returning to the feeding position.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/FT-Series.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(55,4,'Packer','Champion Packer\n\nAn automatic machine suitable for packing piles of clothes.\nWelding capacity 700 mm in length and 680 mm across.\nElectronically adjustable impulse welding, comprising a supply belt with reel holder supports and a pneumatically operated welding bar.\nRetraction tunnel. With a passage of 600 x 400 mm.\nElectrical consumption 12 kW.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/buit.gif',1,NULL,NULL),(56,4,'Finishing items','Tunnel Finisher for drying and finishing of garments model FINTE\n\nCapacities:\nfrom 150 to 1600 garments per hour (polyester-cotton).\n\nModel FINTE/1\n\nModel FINTE STANDARD\n\nTunnel interior in stainless steel individually regulated in the drying chamber.\nIndividual selection of steam spray from the sides and/or underneath in the reception chamber.\nIndividually regulated steam spray in the drying chamber.\nMicroprocessor control with operator terminal and text display. Programmable parameters (temperature, steam spray, garment separation, quantity of garments per hour, etc..) as well as variable regulation of the fan output via inverter.\nPowerful high temperature fan for a quick drying.\nEasy to clean lint screen.\nIn-line transfer free garment transport by means of a screw feed device.\nAutomatic sliding doors at the entry and exit of the machine, pneumatically operated and programme controlled.\nSteam heating, maximum pressure 16 bar.',NULL,'http://www.girbau.com/imgs/productes/series/finte-150.jpg',1,NULL,NULL),(57,4,'Handling - Internal transportation logistics','The appropriate management of internal laundry transportation is one of the most important factors in guaranteeing the profitability of a laundry\n\nIt is not sufficient to have the equipment able to guarantee the best production with the minimum consumption. In the design phase of the laundry, the circulation flow of the laundry has to be studied to be able to optimize the running of the installation.\n\nGirbau prioritizes rationality and takes into account the effects of the laundry circulation flow to improve the laundry’s profitability.\n\nAside from the necessary equipment to improve the logistics of the laundry: aerial loading systems